# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# sentinel-web does NOT require any environment variables to run.
#
# The selfbot API URL and API token are entered through the in-app Settings
# page on first launch and persisted to localStorage. There is nothing to
# inject at build time and nothing for the operator to leak by mistake.
#
# Copy this file to .env.local only if you need to set DESKTOP_BUILD — see
# below. .env.local is in .gitignore so anything you put there stays local.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# ── DO NOT use NEXT_PUBLIC_* for the API token ───────────────────────────────
#
# Earlier docs (and earlier versions of Setup.md) suggested:
#   NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL=...
#   NEXT_PUBLIC_API_KEY=...
#
# DO NOT. `NEXT_PUBLIC_*` env vars are inlined into the client JavaScript
# bundle at build time. Anything you put there is shipped to every visitor
# of the deployed site — including your `API_AUTH_TOKEN`, which is enough
# for anyone to make authenticated calls against your selfbot.
#
# The Settings page stores both values in localStorage so they stay on the
# individual operator's machine and never appear in the bundle.

# ── Build-time only ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# DESKTOP_BUILD=true is set by the sentinel-desktop packaging script when it
# produces a static export for the Electron shell (next.config.ts:isDesktop).
# You should NOT set this manually for a normal web deployment.
#
# DESKTOP_BUILD=

# ── Where the panel connects to (configured at runtime, NOT here) ────────────
#
# The selfbot's CORS allowlist (API_CORS_ORIGINS on the selfbot side) must
# include the origin you serve this panel from. The selfbot ships with the
# following allowlist by default:
#
#   https://sentinel-panel.vercel.app
#   http://localhost:5173
#   http://localhost:3000
#
# For any other origin (your own Vercel deployment, an internal subdomain,
# etc.) set API_CORS_ORIGINS on the selfbot to a comma-separated list
# including your panel origin. A literal "*" reflects any origin — only safe
# if you front the API yourself with another auth layer.

# ── Liveness ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# GET <selfbot URL>/health  is unauthenticated and rate-limit-allowlisted.
# The panel uses it to confirm reachability before the auth handshake.
